This paper discusses the optimization of SPARQL queries, which are used to query RDF graph databases. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases). The paper also discusses the use of optimization methods and cost-based optimization, which are common in the fields of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Data Structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the performance gains that can be obtained through optimization, which is relevant to Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Machine Learning (cs.LG).
